    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="723"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d723">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/12–247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 11, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1501. Chinese reps in Washington have made FLC counter-offer of 17¢ for Zone of
                    Interior supplies for 8⅓ Group Program (Deptel 1457 Dec 2) 20 percent cash with
                    balance payable 5 to 8 years.</p>
                <p>Dept has reiterated to Chinese Emb that because of commitments to other countries
                    17½¢ all cash is minimum acceptable to FLC. It also felt compelled to point out
                    to Chinese Emb that failure of Chinese Govt to act promptly in this matter will
                    inevitably be interpreted as indicating that Chinese professions of urgency of
                    need for military equipment generally have been overemphasized and will
                    therefore serve to delay other matters.</p>
                <p>Pls pass above info to Chief, Air Division, AAG, and in discretion of
                    Minister-Counselor personally to Dr. Wang.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
